    <tags>security agentguard ai coding-agent filesystem windows rust cli</tags>
    <summary>OS-level file safety for AI coding agents</summary>
    <description>
AgentGuard is a Windows security layer that sits between your filesystem and
any AI coding agent — Claude Code, Cursor, OpenCode, Copilot, Windsurf, you
name it. It watches every file operation in real time and enforces exactly
what each agent can read, write, or delete.

Features:
- Real-time agent detection (11+ known agents, 25+ env signals)
- Policy engine with glob-based rules (deny, ask, full, delete, write, read)
- Windows ACL/ACE enforcement
- SQLite audit log with full event history
- Terminal dashboard (TUI, 60fps)
- Invisible background daemon
    </description>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
</package>
